'''Chemical phosphorus removal''' is a wastewater treatment method, where phosphorus is removed using salts of [[aluminum]] (e.g. [[alum]] or poly-aluminum chloride), [[iron]] (e.g. [[ferric chloride]]), or [[calcium]] (e.g. lime). [[Phosphate]] forms precipitates with the metal ions and is removed together with the sludge in the separation unit ([[sedimentation (water treatment)|sedimentation tank]], [[dissolved air flotation|flotation tank]], etc.).
