{{Use British English|date=April 2015}} {{Infobox tunnel |name = Veligonda project tunnel |image = |caption = |location = [[Prakasam district]], [[Andhra Pradesh]], [[India]] |coordinates = {{Coord|15|46|06|N|79|10|50|E|}} |route = Guntur-Kurnool Highway |status = |start = |end = |startwork = May 2005 |open = |close = |owner = |character = |vpd = |construction = |length = {{convert|18.8|km}} | lanes = Two tunnels of 9.2 m and 7 m diameter }}
'''Veligonda Project''' is an under construction irrigation project located in [[Prakasam district]] in [[Andhra Pradesh]], [[India]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://irrigation.cgg.gov.in/OngMaj/Veligonda.htm |title=Andhra Pradesh / Ongole News : Project details |publisher= Irrigation dept, Govt. of A.P. }}</ref> When completed, the project will provide irrigational facilities to 459,000 Acres and drinking water to 1.5 million people in 29 Mandals of fluorine and drought affected areas in [[Prakasam district]], [[Nellore district]] and [[Kadapa district]] by diverting 43.5 TMC of floodwater of [[Krishna River]] from foreshore of Srisailam Reservoir near Kollamvagu and proposed to store in Nallamalasagar Reservoir. The water for the project is drawn through two 18.8&nbsp;km long tunnels across Nallamala hills. The project has been renamed to Poola Subbaiah irrigation project.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/2005/08/01/stories/2005080105540400.htm |title=Andhra Pradesh / `Velugonda' to be named after Poola Subbaiah |publisher=The Hindu |date=2005-08-01 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/work-on-veligonda-project-resumes/article4546486.ece |title=The Hindu: Work on Veligonda project resumes |publisher=TheHindu.com |date=2013-03-25 }}</ref>
The construction includes two parallel tunnels of 18.8&nbsp;km with 9.2 m and 7 m internal diameter and 21.6&nbsp;km Flood flow canal for the water transmission system linking with Srisailam Reservoir up to Guntur-Kurnool road. The project is being implemented by double shielded tunnel boring machine to make the tunnel without disturbing wildlife in the [[Nagarjunsagar-Srisailam Tiger Reserve]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.therobbinscompany.com/en/case-study/veligonda |title=Double Shield bores Water Transfer Tunnel beneath Indian Tiger Sanctuary }}</ref>
==Status of progress of the project== As of June 2018, 15.2 &nbsp;km of tunnel digging had been completed for the first tunnel, and 10.8&nbsp;km had been completed for the second tunnel.
==Expected completion== Only a little progress has been made in the past few years by contractors citing the equipment problems and payment issues with government. Re-tendering of incomplete works is being done by terminating earlier contracts for both tunnels.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.sakshi.com/news/andhra-pradesh/golmal-veligonda-project-tenders-1079190 | title=Re-tendering of Veligonda balance works| accessdate=13 July 2018}}</ref> Completion of first phase works are not expected before December 2019.
